# Content roots to migrate from AEM → Sanity.
#
# This file defines the AEM pages the content CLI walks. For each page, the
# resulting Sanity doc is populated with `slug: { _type: "slug", current: "..." }`
# so the URL lines up with AEM.
#
# Syntax:
#   # ...              → comment (also allowed inline after content)
#   @base /content/... → sets the base path for subsequent slug lines
#   home               → relative slug, joined with the current @base
#   /content/other/top → absolute JCR path (slug = "top", the last segment)
#
# Multiple @base sections are allowed — each @base applies until the next one.
#
# Tip for discovering paths: hit `<AEM_AUTHOR_URL>/content.1.json` while
# logged into AEM author to list top-level site roots. Drill down one level at
# a time (`/content/<sitename>.1.json`, etc.) until you reach your locale.

@base /content/<your-site>/<locale>

home
about
products
support
